# SPRINT 4 BACKLOG

## Sprint Goal
Complete a functional system flow by implementing tournament management and integrating frontend, backend, and database.

## Duration
April 13 - April 27

## User Stories
- As an admin, I want to create tournaments to manage them in the system.
- As a user, I want to view available tournaments.
- As a user, I want the system to work correctly without errors.

## Tasks

### Backend
- [x] Create endpoint to register tournaments
- [x] Create endpoint to retrieve tournaments
- [x] Validate tournament data
- [x] Handle errors in tournament endpoints

### Frontend
- [x] Implement tournament creation form (CreateTournament.jsx)
- [x] Connect form with backend
- [x] Implement tournament list view (TournamentList.jsx)
- [x] Display tournaments from backend
- [x] Show error messages in the UI

### Database
- [x] Verify TOURNAMENTS table structure
- [x] Check relationships with STATUS and USERS
- [x] Test insert and query operations

### Integration
- [x] Connect frontend, backend, and database
- [x] Test complete flow:
      register → login → view → create tournament

## Expected Result
The system will allow user registration, login, and tournament management with a complete functional flow.

## Planned Versions
- [API]-v0.9.5
- [FE]-v0.9.5
- [BE]-v0.9.5

